Running the Notebook as a Workflow
To run the notebook as a workflow in Databricks, follow these steps:

Create a New Job:

Go to the Jobs tab in the Databricks workspace.
Click on "Create Job".
Configure the Job:

Name your job.
Select the notebook you created above.
Choose an existing cluster or create a new one to run the job.
Schedule the Job:

You can schedule the job to run periodically by setting the schedule settings.
Run the Job:

Click "Run Now" to start the job immediately.
Example Workflow Configuration
Job Name: Health News Aggregator
Notebook Path: /Workspace/YourFolder/NewsAggregatorNotebook
Cluster: Choose an existing cluster or create a new one.
Schedule: Set to run every hour, daily, weekly, etc., based on your preference.
